===Etymology===
Borrowed around 1615 from {{bor|en|ar|مُسْلِم||one who submits}}, the {{ar-active participle|nocat=1|noderived=1}} of {{m|ar|أَسْلَمَ||he submitted}}, {{ar-form|IV|verb form}} from the [[triliteral]] root {{ar-root|س|ل|م|nocat=1}}, "to be whole, intact". The verbal noun {{m|ar|إسْلام}} means literally "submission". In a religious sense, {{m|ar|الْإِسْلَام}} translates to "faith, piety", and {{m|ar|مُسْلِم}} to "one who has (religious) faith or piety".

